                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Struggling Learners (Support)</cell>
                        <cell>
                            <line>Provide a summary card with <m>\text{LSF} = k</m>, <m>\text{ASF} = k^2</m>, <m>\text{VSF} = k^3</m>. Use physical cubes to demonstrate. Start with integer scale factors first.</line>
                        </cell>
                        <cell></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>On-Level Learners (Core)</cell>
                        <cell>
                            <line>Complete all phases as described. Include both forward and reverse problems. Use digital checkpoints for immediate feedback.</line>
                        </cell>
                        <cell></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</cell>
                        <cell>
                            <line><alert>Extended Investigation:</alert> If volume increases <m>1000</m> times, <m>\text{LSF} = \sqrt[3]{1000} = 10</m>. A swimming pool model holds <m>0.5</m> L with <m>\text{LSF} = 50</m>.</line>
                        </cell>
                        <cell></cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </axiom>

